projects.description:
A custom-built Python library that provides essential trigonometric functions and utilities for mathematical and scientific computations. The library includes implementations for sine, cosine, tangent, inverse trigonometric functions, angle conversions, and degree-radian calculations. Designed to be simple, efficient, and easy to integrate into any Python project.

Key Features:

Functions for sine, cosine, tangent, and their inverses

Angle conversion between degrees and radians

Error handling for invalid inputs

Lightweight and modular design

Educational implementation for learning core trigonometric principles in Python
projects.title: Trigonmetory library

projects.description:
The Advanced Geometry Library is a Python-based mathematical toolkit designed to perform complex geometric computations with high precision and flexibility. It provides a wide range of functions to calculate areas, perimeters, volumes, angles, distances, and geometric transformations for 2D and 3D shapes.

This library is built to support both educational and scientific applications, offering clean modular code, object-oriented design, and accurate mathematical implementations. It can be used by students, researchers, and developers working on geometry-based projects such as CAD tools, simulations, and mathematical modeling.

 Key Features:

2D shape calculations (Circle, Triangle, Rectangle, Polygon, etc.)

3D shape computations (Sphere, Cylinder, Cone, Cube, etc.)

Distance and midpoint formula implementations

Coordinate geometry (slope, intercept, line intersection, etc.)

Transformation operations: translation, rotation, scaling

Angle and vector operations

Modular and reusable class-based design

Input validation and exception handling
projects.title: Advanced Geomatry Library
